    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA132-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu kāppu mikutikkaṇ āṟṟāḷākiya talaivikkut tōḻi colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">What the confidante said to HER who did not have the strength during the increase of guarding.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA132">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            pērūr tuñcum yāru millait</l>
<l>            tiruntuvāyc cuṟava nīrkāṉ ṟoyyeṉap</l>
<l>            perunteru vutirtaru peyaluṟu taṇvaḷip</l>
<l>            pōramai katavap puraitoṟun tūvak</l>
<l>            kūreyiṟ ṟekiṉa naṭuṅku naṉṉakarp </l>
<l>            payilpaṭa nivanta palpūñ cēkkai</l>
<l>            yayalu māṇciṟai yatuvē yataṉṟalaik</l>
<l>            kāppuṭai vāyil pōṟṟō veṉṉum</l>
<l>            yāmaṅ koḷpavar neṭunā voṇmaṇi</l>
<l>            yoṉṟeṟi pāṇiyi ṉiraṭṭu </l>
<l>            miṉṟuko laḷiyeṉ yāṉpoṉṟu nāḷē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>While the big village is sleeping no one is there.</l>
<l>Even the neighbourhood has glorious defences,</l>
<l rend="indent2">with [its] beds of many flowers that have come up to rustle(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">payil paṭa</term>: why <term xml:lang="ta">paṭu</term> here, when the expression just refers to sound? An auxiliary, but in which function?</note></l>
<l rend="indent2">by the good mansion, where the sharp-toothed dog shivers,</l>
<l rend="indent">as the cool wind, endorsed with raining that drips on the big street,</l>
<l rend="indent2">[sounding] 'oy', [like] a shark vomiting water, with perfect mouth,</l>
<l rend="indent">spatters through every hole in the doors, that are permanently(?) wrapped.</l>
<l rend="indent4">On top of that,</l>
<l>today,</l>
<l rend="indent2">when the long-tongued bright bell of the midnight guards,</l>
<l rend="indent3">that says “protect [your] guarded doors!”,</l>
<l rend="indent2">is sounding in a rhythm beaten one [by one],</l>
<l rend="indent2">[is this] the day I perish, pitiable me?</l>
        </lg>
